      "Title": "Synopsis",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for tpm2-tools is now available for openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP1",
      "Title": "Summary",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "The package contains the code for the TPM (Trusted Platform Module) 2.0 tools based on tpm2-tss.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\ntpm2-tools is the source repository for the Trusted Platform Module (TPM2.0) tools. A malicious attacker can generate arbitrary quote data which is not detected by `tpm2 checkquote`. This issue was patched in version 5.7.(CVE-2024-29038)\n\ntpm2 is the source repository for the Trusted Platform Module (TPM2.0) tools. This vulnerability allows attackers to manipulate tpm2_checkquote outputs by altering the TPML_PCR_SELECTION in the PCR input file.  As a result, digest values are incorrectly mapped to PCR slots and banks, providing a misleading picture of the TPM state. This issue has been patched in version 5.7.(CVE-2024-29039)",
      "Title": "Description",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for tpm2-tools is now available for openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP1.\n\nopenEuler Security has rated this update as having a security impact of medium. A Common Vunlnerability Scoring System(CVSS)base score,which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVElink(s) in the References section.",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "Medium",
      "Title": "Severity",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "tpm2-tools",
      "Title": "Affected Component",
      "Type": "General"
    }
  ],
